.TH "jz4780_nemc_assert" 9 "jz4780_nemc_assert" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
jz4780_nemc_assert \- (de-)assert a NAND device's chip enable pin
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" jz4780_nemc_assert
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int bank "  ","
.BI "bool assert "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
child device of the NEMC.
.IP "bank" 12
bank number of device.
.IP "assert" 12
whether the chip enable pin should be asserted.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
(De-)asserts the chip enable pin for the NAND device connected to the
specified bank.
